ments":12,"created_at":"2020-06-21T16:57:39Z","updated_at":"2020-12-17T00:52:04Z","closed_at":"2020-12-17T00:52:04Z","author_association":"NONE","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"On my system, alacritty is causing about 2.5-3.0 CPU load (according to htop) while only showing a prompt. Other terminals, st for example, show a load of 0.0 when similary idle...\r\n\r\nVia dtrace(1) i gathered the syscalls done by the system, and this showed me, that alacritty generates 2774 syscalls in 3.4s.\r\n\r\nThose are the syscalls generated by alacritty during idle:\r\n```\r\n  compat11.kevent                                                  10\r\n  recvmsg                                                          50\r\n  close                                                           639\r\n  compat11.stat                                                   639\r\n  fstatfs                                                         639\r\n  nanosleep                                                       639\r\n  open                                                            639\r\n  getdirentries                                                  1278\r\n  compat11.lstat                                                 1917\r\n```\r\ntruss(1) showed, that those open/getdirentries calls were done on $HOME/.config/alacritty and the config file it is containing.\r\n\r\nTo me it seems that alacritty is really busy querying its XDG_CONFIG dir and file (at least on FreeBSD).\r\n\r\n### System\r\nOS: FreeBSD 12.1p6\r\nVersion: alacritty 0.4.3\r\nLinux/BSD: X11, Openbox","closed_by":{"login":"chrisduerr","id":8886672,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg4ODY2NzI=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/8886672?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/chrisduerr","html_url":"https://github.com/chrisdue